cs.RO, cs.NI, cs.OS, cs.SY, cs.PL 

Reasoning: 
1. cs.RO (Robotics): The paper focuses on evaluating the Linux communication stack for real-time robotic applications, which falls under the scope of robotics. 
2. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture): The paper evaluates the real-time performance of UDP-based communications on multi-core embedded devices, which involves networking and internet architecture. 
3. cs.OS (Operating Systems): The paper evaluates the Linux communication stack for real-time applications, which falls under the scope of operating systems. 
4. cs.SY (Systems and Control): The paper discusses the reliability of overall robot control, which falls under the scope of systems and control. 
5. cs.PL (Programming Languages): The paper proposes a solution for separating the real-time application and the corresponding interrupt in a CPU, which involves programming languages.
